// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
//
// test/preprocess/p07/pass.test — P7 float reduction per
// `docs/spec/nsl_pp.ebnf` notes (P7 = floats are preprocess-time
// only) + research §5 numeric model + the contract topic table in
// `specs/002-m1-lex-preprocess/contracts/preprocessor-seam.contract.md`.
//
// Topic per the table: "float in `#define` body reduced via
// `_int(...)` before substitution".
//
// Pass shape: a `#define` whose body computes a real value, then
// reduces it to integer via `_int(...)` before substitution. The
// integer literal is what crosses the seam — the intermediate float
// stays preprocess-internal.
//
// Source:
//   `#define HALF _int(_real(8) / 2.0)`
// Helper chain:
//   * `_real(8)`        → 8.0 (real).
//   * `_real(8) / 2.0`  → 4.0 (real).
//   * `_int(4.0)`       → 4 (integer; truncate-toward-zero).
//
// At the use site `%HALF%` splices `4` — integer literal, no
// `tk_dot` and no fractional digits cross.
//
// Tasks.md T043.
//
// **RED state**: the unchanged Phase-3 lexer tokenizes
// `_real`/`_int` as `tk_system_function`, the `/` as
// `tk_slash`, and the `2.0` as `tk_decimal_lit 2 / tk_dot /
// tk_decimal_lit 0` (no float lexer at M1). Phase-4 turns it green.

// RUN: echo '#define HALF _int(_real(8) / 2.0)' >  %t.nsl
// RUN: echo 'reg h = %%HALF%%;'                 >> %t.nsl
// RUN: %nslc -emit=tokens %t.nsl | FileCheck %s

// CHECK:      tk_reg{{[ \t]+}}reg
// CHECK-NEXT: tk_identifier{{[ \t]+}}h
// CHECK-NEXT: tk_assign{{[ \t]+}}=
// CHECK-NEXT: tk_decimal_lit{{[ \t]+}}4
// CHECK-NEXT: tk_semicolon{{[ \t]+}};
// CHECK-NEXT: tk_eof

// No float artifact crosses the seam (P7 + P12):
// CHECK-NOT: tk_dot
// CHECK-NOT: tk_decimal_lit{{[ \t]+}}2
// CHECK-NOT: tk_decimal_lit{{[ \t]+}}8
